```
*White owns the open a-file with a doubled-rook battery and breaks in.*
**FEN:** 5rk1/5ppp/8/8/8/8/R4PPP/R5K1 w - - 0 1
Side to move: White.
[Analyze on Lichess](https://lichess.org/analysis/5rk1/5ppp/8/8/8/8/R4PPP/R5K1_w_-_-_0_1)

White plays **1.Ra8!**, using the rear rook's support to challenge the only defender of the file. After **1...Rxa8 2.Rxa8#** it is checkmate — the recapturing rook reaches the back rank and the king is trapped behind its own f7/g7/h7 pawns. If Black instead declines the trade, White plays **Rxf8+** and emerges a whole rook up. The battery forced its way onto the 8th rank.

